###################################
#  Answer Evaluation 

#evaluation must be completed in the problem text

###################################
#  Solution

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

First use implicit differentiation to find the derivative:
>>[``
  \begin{array}{rcl}
    \dfrac{d}{dx}[x^4 + y^4] &=& \dfrac{d}{dx}[[$c]]\\
  &&\\
    4x^3 + 4y^3\dfrac{dy}{dx} &=& 0\\
  &&\\
    \dfrac{dy}{dx} &=& \dfrac{-4x^3}{4y^3} = -\dfrac{x^3}{y^3}.
  \end{array}
``]<<
Plug in [`x = [$x1]`] and [`y = [$y1]`] to get the slope.:
>>[``
  m = -\dfrac{([$x1])^3}{([$y1])^3} = [$m].
``]<<
Then use point-slope form to find the equation of the tangent line:
>>[``
  y - [$y1] = [$m](x - [$x1]) \; \textrm{or,} \;
  y = [$m] x + [$b].
``]<<

END_PGML_SOLUTION

